<aura:component extends="auradocs:topicPanel">
       <aura:set attribute="title" value="aura:renderIf"/>

       <h1><code>aura:renderIf</code></h1>
       <p>Displays components or other elements if <code>isTrue</code> evaluates to true.</p>

       <p>
       <table>
              <tr>
                     <td><b>Attribute Name</b></td>
                     <td><b>Type</b></td>
                     <td><b>Description</b></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                     <td><code>else</code></td>
                     <td>Component[]</td>
                     <td></td>

              </tr>
              <tr>
                     <td><code>isTrue</code></td>
                     <td>String</td>
                     <td>Required. An expression that determines whether the content is displayed. If it evaluates to true, the content is displayed.</td>
              </tr>
       </table>
       </p>

       <h2>Usage</h2>

       <p>

<auradocs:codeblock>
&lt;aura:attribute name="desc" type="Aura.Component[]"/&gt;
...
&lt;aura:renderif isTrue="<aura:text value="{!"/>v.desc &gt; 0}"&gt;
        &lt;p class="desc"&gt;<aura:text value="{!"/>v.desc}&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/aura:renderif&gt;<br/>
</auradocs:codeblock>

    </p>
    <p>
              The <code>&lt;aura:renderIf&gt;</code> component displays the  elements in the <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> tag
       only if the <code>desc</code> attribute contains a value.
       In other words, the content of the <code>aura:renderIf</code> component will be displayed if the
       <code>isTrue</code> attribute evaluates to true.
       </p>


</aura:component>
